  "body": "It's possible to change the balance of a contract in 3 different ways:\r\n\r\n- Send a transaction to it.\r\n- Send a transaction to it before it has even been deployed.\r\n- Make it the beneficiary of a kill function, which triggers no internal transaction.\r\n\r\nBelow Contracts in use:\r\n\r\n- `StraightPay` sends Ethers to addresses.\r\n- `WithoutValue` is a contract that rejects Ether transfers via transactions.\r\n- `Lethal`'s purpose is to receive value on creation and disburse it on `selfdestruct`.\r\n\r\n**StraightPay.sol**:\r\n\r\n```\r\npragma solidity ^0.4.4;\r\n\r\ncontract StraightPay {\r\n    uint public calls;\r\n\r\n    function StraightPay() payable {}\r\n\r\n    function pay(address whom, uint value)\r\n        returns (bool success) {\r\n        calls++;\r\n        return whom.send(value);\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n**WithoutValue.sol**\r\n\r\n```\r\npragma solidity ^0.4.4;\r\n\r\ncontract WithoutValue {\r\n    function WithoutValue() payable {\r\n        if (msg.value > 0) throw;\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Lethal.sol**\r\n\r\n```\r\npragma solidity ^0.4.4;\r\n\r\ncontract Lethal {\r\n\tfunction Lethal() payable {}\r\n\t\r\n\tfunction kill(address beneficiary) {\r\n\t\tselfdestruct(beneficiary);\r\n\t}\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n_**SafeLethal.sol**_ contract that does not use `selfdestruct` \r\n\r\n```\r\npragma solidity ^0.4.4;\r\n\r\ncontract SafeLethal {\r\n\taddress public owner;\r\n\tbool public killed;\r\n\r\n\tfunction SafeLethal() {\r\n\t\towner = msg.sender;\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n\tfunction kill() isNotKilled {\r\n\t\tif (msg.sender != owner) {\r\n\t\t\tthrow;\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t\tif (!owner.call.value(this.balance)()) {\r\n\t\t\tthrow;\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t\tkilled = true;\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n\tmodifier isNotKilled {\r\n\t\tif (killed) {\r\n\t\t\tthrow;\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t\t_;\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n\tfunction () isNotKilled payable {}\r\n}\r\n```",
